[src:angular/angularjs] Since **`ng-*`** attributes are not valid in HTML specifications, **`data-ng-*`** can also be used as a prefix.
[src:angular/angularjs] For example, both **`ng-app`** and **`data-ng-app`** are valid in AngularJS.
[src:angular/angularjs] AngularJS two-way data binding had its most notable feature, largely relieving the server backend of templating responsibilities.
[src:angular/angularjs] Instead, templates were rendered in plain HTML according to data contained in a scope defined in the model.
[src:angular/angularjs] The `$scope` service in Angular detected changes to the model section and modified HTML expressions in the view via a controller.
[src:angular/angularjs] Likewise, any alterations to the view were reflected in the model.
[src:angular/angularjs] This circumvented the need to actively manipulate the DOM and encouraged bootstrapping and rapid prototyping of web applications.
[src:angular/angularjs] AngularJS detected changes in models by comparing the current values with values stored earlier in a process of dirty-checking, unlike Ember.js and Backbone.js that triggered listeners when the model values are changed.
